MISCELLANEOUS DISMISSALS

2006-2239. State ex rel. Cincinnati Enquirer v. Riley.

In Mandamus. This cause originated in this court on the filing of a complaint for a writ of mandamus. Upon consideration of relator’s application for a partial dismissal,

It is ordered by the court that the application for partial dismissal is granted. Count Two of relator’s complaint is dismissed.

This action remains pending before the court on Count One of relator’s complaint.
